        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:37PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sharon, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
South Tunbridge, West Fairlee, West Fairlee Center, Bradford,
Tunbridge, East Bethel, North Tunbridge, Vershire, Sharon, Thetford
Hill State Park, Ely, Thetford Center, South Randolph, West Norwich,
Union Village Dam Recreation Area, South Newbury, West Hartford,
North Royalton, East Barnard, and Thetford Hill.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 89 between mile markers 8 and 26.
Interstate 91 between mile markers 77 and 103.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and southern Vermont.</instruction>
